### Test Group Management API
### Make sure the backend is running on localhost:3000

### 1. Login to get token (replace with your credentials)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "your-email@example.com",
  "password": "your-password"
}

### 2. Create a new group (replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN with actual token from step 1)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/groups
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

{
  "name": "Family Savings Circle",
  "description": "Monthly savings for family emergencies",
  "contributionAmount": 100,
  "frequency": "MONTHLY",
  "payoutMethod": "SEQUENTIAL",
  "maxMembers": 5
}

### 3. Get all groups for user
GET http://localhost:3000/api/groups
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### 4. Get group by ID (replace GROUP_ID with actual group id from step 2)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/groups/GROUP_ID
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### 5. Join group with invite code (requires second user - register another user first)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/groups/join
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer SECOND_USER_JWT_TOKEN

{
  "inviteCode": "INVITE_CODE_FROM_STEP_2"
}

### 6. Update group details (owner only)
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/groups/GROUP_ID
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

{
  "name": "Updated Family Savings",
  "contributionAmount": 150
}

### 7. Start group (owner only, when full)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/groups/GROUP_ID/start
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### 8. Delete/Cancel group (owner only, before start)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/groups/GROUP_ID
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN
